title._content: MT Atlantic Duchess - General Arrangement Profile Plan

description._content:
Launched: 1950
Owners: S. Livanos (Greece)
End of service: 1975. Broken up, Split, Croatia.
Motor tanker blew up in 1951 discharging her cargo of oil at Swansea and broke in half. The two parts were towed to the Graythorp Yard on the River Tees, rejoined and other damage repaired.
